ure became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705197,"age":0,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705201,"age":94,"year":"1549","julianDay":2286821,"title":"Book of Common Prayer","description":"Book of Common Prayer, a product of the English Reformation, was published in 1549 for assistance in the administration of the sacraments and other rites and ceremonies of the church according to the use of the Church of England. The book outlined morning, evening, and communion prayers and orders for baptism and marriage, thus making England a truly Protestant state.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Book_of_Common_Prayer","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Book of Common Prayer","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705202,"age":103,"year":"1558","julianDay":2290108,"title":"Act of Uniformity","description":"The Act of Uniformity was passed by the Parliament of England and required all people to go to church once a week. The consequence of not attending church was a fine of 12 pence, which was a considerable amount for a poor person.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"William Bayle was born in 1455, in Urchfont, Wiltshire, England. He had at least 1 daughter with Bayle. He died in Chittoe, Wiltshire, England."},"et":{"1455–":"1455–Surnud","1460–Female":"1460–Surnud","1480–1540":"1480–1540","1455–Male":"1455–Surnud","1558":"1558","1455":"1455","1540":"1540","1460":"1460","1480":"1480","1549":"1549","Stafford, Staffordshire, England":"Stafford, Staffordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Urchfon